    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Albany</placeName>
                <date>Dec. 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1862</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your favor of the <date>2d</date> inst with receipt<lb/> for $14 due
                you, has been received and enclosed you<lb/> will find a Draft on <persName>Mess.
                    Hamm &amp; Rosenheim</persName> of <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> for that
                amount. In regard to the Portuguese Machsorim<lb/> I regret that the price is too
                high for me to purchase,<lb/>â€”if I could get the best Binding for $20 I should
                be<lb/> willing to pay that amount, but as it is I must forego<lb/> my intention as
                I do not want it for myself</p>
            <p>My eldest daughter <persName>Leah</persName> is married to <persName>Mr. S.
                    Hamm</persName><lb/> of <placeName>New York</placeName> and lives at
                    <placeName>No 54 West 22d <sic>st.</sic></placeName> I shall<lb/> be very happy
                to see you here next summer or any<lb/> other time. My wife &amp; son send their
                respects and<lb/> they as well as myself desire to be kindly remembered<lb/> by
                you</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Yours Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">Louis Spanier</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">pr <persName>E. S.</persName></p>
        </body>
